# Vercel Speed Insights Implementation

## Summary
Successfully installed and configured Vercel Speed Insights for this Next.js 15.1.0 project using the App Router.

## Changes Made

### 1. Package Installation
- Installed `@vercel/speed-insights` version 1.3.1 using npm
- Updated `package.json` to include the new dependency
- Updated `package-lock.json` with dependency tree

### 2. Code Integration
Modified `src/app/layout.tsx`:
- Added import statement: `import { SpeedInsights } from "@vercel/speed-insights/next";`
- Added `<SpeedInsights />` component inside the `<body>` tag, placed after `{children}` component
- Follows Next.js 13.5+ App Router best practices

## Implementation Details

### Why This Approach
- The project uses Next.js 15.1.0 with App Router, which is version 13.5+
- Used the appropriate import path: `@vercel/speed-insights/next`
- No need for 'use client' directive or `usePathname()` as this is the recommended approach for App Router
- The component is placed in the root layout to track all pages

### File Structure
```
web/
├── package.json (updated with @vercel/speed-insights dependency)
├── package-lock.json (updated with full dependency tree)
└── src/app/layout.tsx (added SpeedInsights component)
```

## Verification

### Build Success
- ✅ Project builds successfully with no errors
- ✅ Type checking passed
- ✅ Linting completed during build process
- ✅ Static page generation completed (4/4 pages)
- ✅ Export completed successfully

### Changes Staged
The following files have been staged for commit:
- `package.json` - Added @vercel/speed-insights dependency
- `package-lock.json` - Updated lockfile with dependency resolution
- `src/app/layout.tsx` - Added SpeedInsights component

## Notes
- The SpeedInsights component will automatically track page views and Web Vitals metrics
- No additional configuration is required for basic functionality
- The component only sends data when deployed on Vercel (no impact in local development)
- Metrics will be available in the Vercel dashboard under the Speed Insights tab
